---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portrait from '../assets/portrait-Marion.jpg';
import saraTissenier from '../assets/sara-tissenier.jpeg';
import jeremyPinhel from '../assets/jeremy-pinhel.jpeg';
import christinaStumpf from '../assets/christina-stumpf.jpeg';

const teammates = [
  {
    photo: saraTissenier.src,
    quote: "Je travaille avec Marion depuis plusieurs années et elle fait clairement partie des PM avec qui on a envie de travailler. Elle fait preuve d'une grande maturité produit et sait arbitrer avec justesse sous pression marché, en alignant enjeux business, besoins utilisateurs et qualité de ce qui est délivré, sans jamais perdre de vue l'humain au sein de ses équipes. Elle collabore très étroitement avec le design et sait en faire un véritable levier d'impact produit. Curieuse et à l'aise avec la technique, elle expérimente et s'approprie les innovations, notamment en IA, pour améliorer ses façons de travailler. Un vrai plaisir de collaborer avec elle au quotidien.",
    name: 'Sara Tissenier',
    role: 'Senior Product Designer, AI product',
    context: 'Same team @ Toucan',
    date: 'January 7, 2026',
    linkedin: 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/saratissenier/',
  },
  {
    photo: jeremyPinhel.src,
    quote: "J'ai eu la chance de travailler avec Marion pendant plus d'un an dans la même squad, et c'est probablement l'une des collaborations produit / engineering les plus riches que j'ai connues. Ce que j'ai beaucoup apprécié avec Marion, c'est qu'elle ne reste jamais en surface des sujets. Elle cherche vraiment à comprendre : les utilisateurs, le marché, la concurrence, mais aussi les contraintes techniques et les impacts côté engineering. Ça rend les discussions très concrètes, très efficaces, et surtout beaucoup plus intéressantes pour un développeur. On a notamment travaillé ensemble sur toucanai.cloud, un nouveau produit pensé AI-first, dans un domaine où tout était encore très exploratoire. Côté engineering, c'est une PM avec qui il est très agréable de travailler. Je retravaillerais avec Marion sans aucune hésitation.",
    name: 'Jérémy Pinhel',
    role: 'Senior Software Engineer',
    context: 'Same team @ Toucan',
    date: 'May 4, 2026',
    linkedin: 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeremypinhel/',
  },
  {
    photo: christinaStumpf.src,
    quote: "Marion worked on Content Marketing tasks for the French market while being in my SEO team at FlixBus. She is very passionate about anything she does. She has lots of great and relevant ideas that drive the business forward and pushes all her projects with great vigour. On top of that, Marion is a great team player and a fun person to be around. Thank you, Marion, for all your incredible work, dedication, reliability and spirit!",
    name: 'Christina Stumpf',
    role: 'Project Lead Legal Tech @ Flix',
    context: 'Direct manager @ FlixBus',
    date: 'June 15, 2018',
    linkedin: 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/christina-stumpf-584a8873/',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Marion Débonnaire — PM · AI-native Analytics"
  description="Product Manager specialised in AI-native embedded analytics SaaS. I turn data complexity into product clarity."
>

  <!-- ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-content">

        <h1 class="hero-title">
          Senior Product Manager<br />
          <em class="hero-em">at the edge of AI.</em>
        </h1>

        <p class="hero-subtitle">
          6 years shipping SaaS and mobile products, at the intersection of data, Artificial Intelligence, and user obsession. Currently building the next generation of AI-native analytics at Toucan Toco.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="/portfolio" class="btn btn-primary">See my work</a>
          <a href="/my-story" class="btn btn-outline">My story</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-value">6+</span>
            <span class="stat-label text-muted">Years in product</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-divider"></div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-value">3</span>
            <span class="stat-label text-muted">AI-native products shipped</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-divider"></div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-value">B2B</span>
            <span class="stat-label text-muted">SaaS focus</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-visual">
        <div class="portrait-frame">
          <Image
            src={portrait}
            alt="Marion Débonnaire, Product Manager"
            width={480}
            height={580}
            class="portrait-img"
            loading="eager"
          />
          <div class="portrait-overlay"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-scroll" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="scroll-line"></span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Value Props ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="value-props">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">What I bring to the table</h2>
        <p class="section-sub text-muted">
          Three domains. One through-line: making complex data systems feel effortless.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="props-grid">
        <article class="card prop-card">
          <div class="prop-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>AI product strategy</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Defining where AI creates durable value vs. hype. I've shipped LLM features that
            users actually rely on — not demos that fade after launch.
          </p>
          <a href="/ai-expertise" class="prop-link">
            Explore my AI work
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </a>
        </article>

        <article class="card prop-card">
          <div class="prop-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M9 21V9"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Embedded analytics</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Building analytics that live inside the product, not beside it. From chart libraries
            to semantic layers — I speak both PM and data engineering.
          </p>
          <a href="/portfolio" class="prop-link">
            See case studies
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </a>
        </article>

        <article class="card prop-card">
          <div class="prop-icon">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>0→1 execution</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            From fuzzy problem space to shipped product. I thrive in ambiguity and have a track
            record of leading cross-functional teams from discovery to revenue impact.
          </p>
          <a href="/my-story" class="prop-link">
            Read my story
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Selected Work ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="selected-work">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header section-header--row">
        <div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Selected work</h2>
          <p class="section-sub text-muted">A few stories worth telling.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/portfolio" class="btn btn-outline">All projects</a>
      </div>

      <div class="work-list">
        <a href="/portfolio" class="work-item card">
          <div class="work-meta">
            <span class="tag accent">AI · Analytics</span>
            <span class="work-year text-muted">2024</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="work-title">Natural Language to Insight</h3>
          <p class="text-muted work-desc">
            Shipped an LLM-powered query interface on top of a multi-tenant analytics platform,
            reducing time-to-insight by 60% for non-technical users.
          </p>
          <div class="work-arrow">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/portfolio" class="work-item card">
          <div class="work-meta">
            <span class="tag">B2B SaaS · Data</span>
            <span class="work-year text-muted">2023</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="work-title">Embedded Analytics SDK</h3>
          <p class="text-muted work-desc">
            Designed and launched a white-label analytics SDK adopted by 40+ enterprise clients
            within the first two quarters.
          </p>
          <div class="work-arrow">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/portfolio" class="work-item card">
          <div class="work-meta">
            <span class="tag">Platform · Growth</span>
            <span class="work-year text-muted">2022</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="work-title">Self-serve Data Onboarding</h3>
          <p class="text-muted work-desc">
            Rebuilt the onboarding flow for a data platform from zero, cutting time-to-value
            from 3 weeks to under 2 days.
          </p>
          <div class="work-arrow">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── GitHub Activity ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="github-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="github-inner card">
        <div class="github-header">
          <div class="github-text">
            <span class="github-label text-muted">I don't just spec, I ship.</span>
            <h2 class="github-title">Building in public</h2>
            <p class="text-muted github-desc">From data pipelines to product prototypes, I use code as a thinking tool. This portfolio is built and maintained by me.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="github-meta">
            <a href="https://github.com/MarionDebo" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline github-btn">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 0C5.374 0 0 5.373 0 12c0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23A11.509 11.509 0 0112 5.803c1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576C20.566 21.797 24 17.3 24 12c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
              View on GitHub
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="github-graph">
          <div class="calendar"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Kind Words ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="kind-words">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">Kind words from teammates</h2>
        <p class="section-sub text-muted">From people I've shipped with.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="kw-grid">
        {teammates.map(t => (
          <figure class="card kw-card">
            <div class="quote-mark" aria-hidden="true">"</div>
            <blockquote class="kw-quote">{t.quote}</blockquote>
            <figcaption class="kw-author">
              {t.linkedin
                ? <a href={t.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label={`${t.name} on LinkedIn`}>
                    <img src={t.photo} alt={t.name} class={`kw-avatar${t.name === 'Sara Tissenier' ? ' kw-avatar--bordered' : ''}`} width="56" height="56" loading="lazy" />
                  </a>
                : <img src={t.photo} alt={t.name} class={`kw-avatar${t.name === 'Sara Tissenier' ? ' kw-avatar--bordered' : ''}`} width="56" height="56" loading="lazy" />
              }
              <div>
                {t.linkedin
                  ? <a href={t.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="kw-name kw-name--link">{t.name}</a>
                  : <p class="kw-name">{t.name}</p>
                }
                <p class="kw-role text-muted">{t.role}</p>
                {t.date && <p class="kw-date text-muted">{t.date}</p>}
              </div>
            </figcaption>
            {t.context && <p class="kw-context">{t.context}</p>}
          </figure>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-box card">
        <div class="cta-content">
          <h2>Let's build something that matters</h2>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Whether you're scaling a data product, rethinking your AI strategy, or need
            a PM who can hold a conversation with your data team — I'd love to hear from you.
          </p>
          <a href="mailto:hello@mariondebonnaire.com" class="btn btn-primary">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="2" y="4" width="20" height="16" rx="2"/><path d="m22 7-8.97 5.7a1.94 1.94 0 01-2.06 0L2 7"/></svg>
            Get in touch
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.hero {
  padding-top: calc(var(--space-20) + var(--space-8));
  padding-bottom: var(--space-20);
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Soft navy blob top-right */
.hero::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: -160px;
  right: -160px;
  width: 600px;
  height: 600px;
  background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(15,23,42,0.06) 0%, transparent 60%);
  pointer-events: none;
}

.hero-inner {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: var(--space-16);
  align-items: center;
}

/* Badge */
.hero-badge {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-2);
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
  border-radius: var(--radius-full);
  border: 1.5px solid var(--glass-border);
  background: var(--glass-bg);
  backdrop-filter: var(--glass-blur);
  font-size: var(--text-xs);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
}

.badge-dot {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--color-accent);
  animation: pulse 2s infinite;
}

@keyframes pulse {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
  50% { opacity: 0.35; }
}

/* Title */
.hero-title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(var(--text-3xl), 4vw, var(--text-5xl));
  font-weight: 800;
  line-height: var(--leading-tight);
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
}

.hero-em {
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: 300;
  color: var(--color-accent);
}

.hero-subtitle {
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  max-width: 480px;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
}

.hero-actions {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-3);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
}

/* Stats */
.hero-stats {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-6);
}

.stat-value {
  display: block;
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--color-accent);
}

.stat-label { font-size: var(--text-xs); }

.stat-divider {
  width: 1px;
  height: 32px;
  background: var(--color-border-soft);
}

/* Portrait */
.hero-visual {
  position: relative;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}

.portrait-frame {
  position: relative;
  border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  overflow: hidden;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 420px;
  aspect-ratio: 4/5;
  border: 1.5px solid var(--glass-border);
  box-shadow: var(--glass-shadow);
}

.portrait-img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: top center;
}

.portrait-overlay {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(15,23,42,0.2) 0%, transparent 55%);
}

/* Scroll indicator */
.hero-scroll {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: var(--space-8);
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}

.scroll-line {
  width: 1px;
  height: 48px;
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-accent), transparent);
  animation: scrollAnim 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes scrollAnim {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 0.2; transform: scaleY(1); }
  50% { opacity: 0.7; transform: scaleY(1.2); }
}

/* ── Section shared ──────────────────────────────────── */
.section-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
}

.section-header--row {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-end;
  justify-content: space-between;
  text-align: left;
}

.section-title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-3xl);
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
}

.section-sub {
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  max-width: 480px;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

/* ── Value Props ─────────────────────────────────────── */
.value-props {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
}

.props-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: var(--space-6);
}

.prop-card { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-4); }

.prop-icon {
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  background: var(--color-accent-light);
  color: var(--color-accent);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-accent-mid);
}

.prop-card h3 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
}

.prop-link {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-1);
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  margin-top: auto;
  transition: gap var(--transition);
}

.prop-link:hover { gap: var(--space-2); }

/* ── Work list ───────────────────────────────────────── */
.selected-work { background: transparent; }
.work-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-3); }

.work-item.card { padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6); }

.work-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
  grid-template-rows: auto auto;
  gap: var(--space-2) var(--space-8);
  align-items: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color var(--transition), transform var(--transition);
}

.work-item:hover { transform: translateX(4px); }

.work-meta {
  grid-row: 1;
  grid-column: 1;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-3);
}

.work-title {
  grid-row: 1;
  grid-column: 2;
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-xl);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}

.work-desc {
  grid-row: 2;
  grid-column: 1 / 3;
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
}

.work-year { font-size: var(--text-xs); }

.work-arrow {
  grid-row: 1 / 3;
  grid-column: 3;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  transition: color var(--transition), transform var(--transition);
}

.work-item:hover .work-arrow {
  color: var(--color-accent);
  transform: translateX(4px);
}

/* ── CTA ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cta-section { background: transparent; }

.cta-box {
  text-align: center;
  padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-8);
}

.cta-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }

.cta-box h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-3xl);
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
}

.cta-box p {
  max-width: 520px;
  margin-inline: auto;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
}

/* ── GitHub Activity ─────────────────────────────────── */
.github-section { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.28); }

.github-inner {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--space-8);
}

.github-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--space-8);
}

.github-meta {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-6);
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.github-meta p {
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  max-width: 320px;
}

.github-graph {
  width: 100%;
  overflow: hidden;
  padding: var(--space-4);
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
}

.github-label {
  display: block;
  font-size: var(--text-xs);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
}

